  "title": "Tech Support Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Title: Tech Support Engineer (AV Solutions)</strong><br /></p><p><strong>About the Role:</strong></p><p>We are seeking a hands-on and detail-oriented AV Engineer to support and manage Audio Visual projects focused on visual solutions such as digital signage, LED video walls, smart office systems, IPTV, and network infrastructure and more.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Objective:</strong></p><ul><li>To deliver proposed solutions and services through working closely with internal teams, manufacturers, subcontractors, and suppliers.</li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Manage, collaborate, and work with internal Sales and Technical team, and external parties like, Consultant, Main Contractor, Subcontractor, Manufacturer, and Supplier.</li><li>Study schematic design and drawings to produce Audio Visual drawings</li><li>Manage Project schedules, Project budgets, changes in order, Bill of Material</li><li>Manage customer’s expectations and deliver customer experience</li><li>Plan, manage and schedule resources.</li><li>Handle installation, testing, commissioning, and technical troubleshooting</li><li>Assist in tender preparation and documentation</li><li>Source for new and emerging Audio-Visual solutions to enhance company’s offerings</li><li>Conduct training to end users on implemented solutions</li><li>Conduct demo presentations on company’s offerings</li></ul><p><strong>Educational Qualifications:</strong></p><ul><li>Min. ITE/Diploma in IT/Engineering/Audio Visual or related fields</li></ul><p><strong>Experience:</strong></p><ul><li>Fresh graduate welcome to apply</li><li>Able to work independently in the fast moving and challenging environment</li><li>Good Communication and Interpersonal skills</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office; Photoshop and basic networking knowledge are a plusStrong coordination, documentation, and problem-solving skills</li><li>Able to work independently and collaboratively</li></ul>",
